אנן לקולא גמרינן? Atu anan l'kula gamrinan? What do you mean? You

1158
00:55:42,480 --> 00:55:45,340
think we're being lenient based on a hundred and sixty? לחומרא קא

1159
00:55:45,340 --> 00:55:47,960
גמרינן, L'chumra ka gamrinan, we're being strict. דאורייתא ברובא בטיל, D'Oraisa b'ruva

1160
00:55:47,960 --> 00:55:52,320
bateil, again same as before. Without this learning of from איל בשילא

1161
00:55:51,640 --> 00:55:55,800
Ayil Bashila we would have said that biblically you go by majority.

1162
00:55:55,800 --> 00:55:58,320
Why? According to רש''י Rashi because there's no idea of טעם biblically,

1163
00:55:58,320 --> 00:56:01,320
according to the תוספות Tosafot and everybody else there is an idea

1164
00:56:01,320 --> 00:56:03,580
of טעם but it's all the same taste. So therefore you would

1165
00:56:03,580 --> 00:56:07,540
not have needed. And therefore this is telling us a stringency that

1166
00:56:07,540 --> 00:56:10,400
it's not enough to have רוב, rov, even when it all tastes

1167
00:56:10,400 --> 00:56:13,420
the same you need sixty or a hundred. And again תוספות Tosafot

1168
00:56:13,420 --> 00:56:16,480
says that's all דרבנן because that's really a stand-in, really when it's

1169
00:56:16,480 --> 00:56:19,580
the same מין במינו you really only do need רוב rov biblically.

1170
00:56:19,580 --> 00:56:21,960
But anyway תוספות Tosafot says it's all דרבנן. But again another way

1171
00:56:21,960 --> 00:56:24,960
of reading this is even if we admit to תוספות that taste

1172
00:56:24,960 --> 00:56:28,957
is not—is biblical and here it all tastes the same, maybe this

1173
00:56:28,957 --> 00:56:32,160
is teaching you that independent of taste there's another concern of quantity

1174
00:56:32,160 --> 00:56:34,880
and of proportions and of a hundred and sixty.
